description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/kiss_transport.c
Lines: 279-346

In dispatch_frame(), the stats mutex is locked/unlocked multiple times:

    k_mutex_lock(&ctx->stats_mutex, K_FOREVER);
    ctx->stats.rx_frames++;
    k_mutex_unlock(&ctx->stats_mutex);
    ...
    if (port == KISS_PORT_AX25) {
        k_mutex_lock(&ctx->stats_mutex, K_FOREVER);
        ctx->stats.rx_data_port0++;
        k_mutex_unlock(&ctx->stats_mutex);
        ...
    }

This pattern appears 7+ times in the function. Each lock/unlock pair:
1. Has overhead from context switches
2. Allows interleaving between stat updates (non-atomic multi-field updates)
3. Could be consolidated into one lock region

While not a bug per se, this creates inconsistent statistics if queried mid-dispatch (rx_frames incremented but rx_data_port0 not yet).

Fix: Acquire stats_mutex once at the start of dispatch_frame, update all relevant stats, then unlock once at the end.
